message.content: We refer to Wikipedia articles on medicine for help. The patient presents with vaginal bleeding during pregnancy and a history of cesarean delivery, which increases the risk of placenta previa. Therefore, ultrasound examination would be ordered to check for placental location. Partial covering of the internal cervical os by the placental edge is the characteristic finding in placenta previa. Retroplacental blood accumulation and placental calcification are not specific to this condition, and cysts on the placental surface are not a normal finding.
